 redshift distributions is\ncomplemented with an independent clustering redshift approach. After validation\nof the clustering-$z$ on the same mock catalogues and a careful assessment of\nsystematic errors, we find no significant bias of the SOM redshift\ndistributions with respect to the clustering-$z$ measurements. The SOM redshift\ndistributions re-calibrated by the clustering-$z$ represent an alternative\ncalibration of the redshift distributions with only slightly larger\nuncertainties in the mean redshifts of $\\sim 0.01-0.02$ to be used in KiDS-1000\ncosmological weak lensing analyses. As this includes the SOM uncertainty,\nclustering-$z$ are shown to be fully competitive on KiDS-1000 data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Jul 2020 17:55:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Jan 2021 16:12:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-24"}
