 (r.l.u.), a large correlation length of about 40\nnm, and a predominant dz2 orbital character, instead of the typical dx2-y2\ncharacter. Its appearance is determined by the hole doping of the manganite\nwhich is a key parameter controlling the interfacial charge transfer and\norbital reconstruction. We anticipate that the observation of a previously\nunknown type of density wave order at the YBCO interface will allow for fresh\nperspectives on the enigmatic relation between superconductivity and charge\norder (CO) in the cuprates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 Jul 2020 08:04:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-18"}
